<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE showme.pack	SYSTEM "../Symbols.dtd">
<showme.pack xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
	xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
	xmlns="http://webmath.math.ualberta.ca/v1/Example"
	xsi:schemaLocation="http://webmath.math.ualberta.ca/v1/Example    http://webmath.math.ualberta.ca/Schemas/v1/Example.xsd"
	id="Exa_Minor">
	<texsupport href="../LinearAlgebraTeXSupport.xml"/>
	
	<title>Minors of a Matrix: Examples</title>
	
	<showme>
		<statement>
			<para>The matrix</para>
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
\Mtrx{A} = 
\left[
\begin{array}{rrrr}
4 & 1 & 6 & 5 \\
3 & -2 & -3 & 2 \\
9 & 2 & 4 & 7 \\
1 & -9 & -3 & 1
\end{array}
\right]
]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
			
			<para>has as its <latex>(1,3)</latex>-minor the matrix <latex>\Mtrx{A}_{13}</latex> below. The <latex>1</latex>st row and the <latex>3</latex>rd column of <latex>\Mtrx{A}</latex> have been omitted.</para>
			
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
\Mtrx{A}_{13} = 
\left[
\begin{array}{rrr}
3 & -2  & 2 \\
9 & 2 & 7 \\
1 & -9 & 1
\end{array}
\right]
]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
			
			<para>For another example, the <latex>(4,2)</latex>-minor of <latex>\Mtrx{A}</latex> is</para>
			
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
\Mtrx{A}_{42} = 
\left[
\begin{array}{rrrr}
4 & 6 & 5 \\
3 & -3 & 2 \\
9 & 4 & 7 
\end{array}
\right]
]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
			<para>The <latex>4</latex>th row and the <latex>2</latex>nd column of <latex>\Mtrx{A}</latex> have been omitted.</para>
		</statement>
	</showme>
</showme.pack>